explain select sum(c1) over (partition by c3) from (select * from t1 order by c3);
Query Plan
========================================
|ID|OPERATOR       |NAME|EST. ROWS|COST|
----------------------------------------
|0 |WINDOW FUNCTION|    |5        |44  |
|1 | SUBPLAN SCAN  |    |5        |43  |
|2 |  SORT         |    |5        |43  |
|3 |   TABLE SCAN  |t1  |5        |37  |
========================================

Outputs & filters: 
-------------------------------------
  0 - output([T_FUN_SUM(.c1)]), filter(nil), 
      win_expr(T_FUN_SUM(.c1)), partition_by([.c3]), order_by(nil), window_type(RANGE), upper(UNBOUNDED PRECEDING), lower(UNBOUNDED FOLLOWING)
  1 - output([.c1], [.c3]), filter(nil), 
      access([.c1], [.c3])
  2 - output([t1.c1], [t1.c3]), filter(nil), sort_keys([t1.c3, ASC])
  3 - output([t1.c1], [t1.c3]), filter(nil), 
      access([t1.c1], [t1.c3]), partitions(p0)

explain select sum(c1) over (order by c1,c2,c3) from (select * from t1 order by c1,c2,c3);
